ts should focus on core APIs.\\\" \\n\\nIf there's no action, I could leave it empty. I need to ensure I have enough research on artifact dependencies and documentation. A summary could highlight that Janino core APIs run in-process and clarify the absence of Docker or environment properties for compilations in version 3.1.0.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"Janino 3.1.0 core usage is in-process Java compilation/evaluation and its required commons-compiler artifact is already a normal transitive dependency of org.codehaus.janino:janino; no Docker image, extra dependency, environment variable, or system property is needed for meaningful coverage. The observed javac failure is a stale test import: iterator utilities moved from org.codehaus.janino.util.iterator to org.codehaus.commons.compiler.util.iterator.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Avoid basing tests on removed org.codehaus.janino.util.* packages from 3.0.x; for 3.1.0 the shared utility packages are under org.codehaus.commons.compiler.*.\",\n    \"Optional Ant integration classes may require Apache Ant, but they are not necessary for meaningful Janino coverage and should be avoided unless intentionally testing Ant-specific integration.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a974645deb05e19016a42b1e40e688190bf1ab24a7cf48edd\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3851, "output": 724, "cacheRead": 16896, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21471, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782755798053, "responseId": "resp_0a974645deb05e19016a42b1d6984c81908226be5a08ed7eda"}}
